# {{.Title}} — a octarq plugin

Scaffolded with `octarq plugin new {{.Name}}`. A octarq plugin is one repo with
two mirror halves, composed into a host binary **at build time** (the xcaddy
model — no fork, no `internal/*` imports).

```
{{.Name}}.go     Go half — implements plugin.Plugin (Name / Models / Mount)
web/             JS half — a UIPlugin against @octarq/plugin-sdk
```

## Build

```bash
go mod tidy                       # fetch github.com/octarq-org/octarq
go build ./...                    # compile the Go half
```

## Compose it into a octarq binary

Point the host's plugin manifest at this module and build:

```bash
OCTARQ_PLUGINS='[{"go":"{{.Module}}","npm":"{{.NpmName}}"}]' make plugin-build
```

The Go half mounts at `{{.RoutePrefix}}/…`; the web half adds a `/{{.Name}}`
page and a sidebar entry. Replace the `ping` endpoint and the page with your own
feature.
